WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:04.648 --> 00:01:08.484
- [Clattering]
- [Mutters] What's that?

3
00:01:08.569 --> 00:01:11.154
[Moans. Sighs]

4
00:01:11.238 --> 00:01:13.322
It sounds like
the garbageman.

5
00:01:13.407 --> 00:01:16.951
- [Sighs] Oh? On Tuesday?
- [Yawns]

6
00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:21.122
Maybe they changed
the schedule.

7
00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:24.333
- [Moans]
- [Sighs] Oh. shit.

8
00:01:25.544 --> 00:01:27.754
[Sighs]

9
00:01:27.838 --> 00:01:30.339
[Clattering]

10
00:01:38.474 --> 00:01:41.559
Oh! Wait a minute!
Wait a minute!

11
00:01:41.643 --> 00:01:43.686
Hey! Hold it up.
you guys.

12
00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:50.693
[Brakes Hissing]

13
00:01:53.155 --> 00:01:55.406
I was afraid you'd miss me.

14
00:01:56.784 --> 00:01:58.868
Don't worry. We won't.

15
00:02:00.162 --> 00:02:03.039
[Groaning]

16
00:02:15.636 --> 00:02:17.970
[Man]
Now that is American workmanship.

17
00:02:18.055 --> 00:02:21.557
You think the Japanese invented that?
Bullshit. We did.

18
00:02:21.642 --> 00:02:24.393
Oh. for a while there we lost it.
but we got it back.

19
00:02:24.478 --> 00:02:28.731
- I like Cadillacs.
- You like Cadillacs? Come around.
brother. get in this Cadillac.

20
00:02:28.816 --> 00:02:30.233
You're gonna love it.

21
00:02:30.317 --> 00:02:32.235
This is style and beauty.

22
00:02:34.488 --> 00:02:38.074
Comfy. right? Oh. I know what
you're gonna say. That's vinyl.

23
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:41.160
Take it from me. you don't want
leather. brother. Leather's hot.

24
00:02:41.245 --> 00:02:44.747
It's uncomfortable. It cracks. Nothing
but trouble. Look at the headroom in here.

25
00:02:44.832 --> 00:02:47.834
- [Engine Starts]
- A guy like you is not gonna have any problem.

26
00:02:47.918 --> 00:02:51.504
Go ahead. start it up.
Listen to that. That's power.

27
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:54.507
- That's performance.
- You know what I like best?

28
00:02:54.591 --> 00:02:58.469
- What's that?
- The price.

29
00:02:58.554 --> 00:03:00.596
- [Tires Screech]
- Hey! Wait a minute!

30
00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:02.807
You can't
drive that car in here!

31
00:03:02.891 --> 00:03:06.310
Whoa! Whoa!

32
00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:16.404
- [Chattering]
- [Tires Screeching]

33
00:03:27.541 --> 00:03:30.459
- Hey. guys. how's it going?
- Hey!

34
00:03:30.544 --> 00:03:32.545
Workin'. Workin'.

35
00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.316
[Engine Starts]

36
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:38.421
Oh. Daddy. put me down!
[Laughs]

37
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:40.923
- I surrender. Surrender. [Laughs]
- [Indistinct]

38
00:05:48.265 --> 00:05:52.268
[No Audible Dialogue]

39
00:06:58.418 --> 00:07:02.421
[Laughter]

40
00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:29.031
I love you too.

41
00:07:43.255 --> 00:07:46.215
Here come the sandwiches.

42
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:50.553
Why don't they just call him
"Girl George"?

43
00:07:50.637 --> 00:07:52.638
It would cut down
all the confusion.

44
00:07:52.722 --> 00:07:55.558
Oh. Dad. that's so old.

45
00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:02.231
When I was a boy and rock and roll
came to East Germany...

46
00:08:02.315 --> 00:08:04.358
the Communists said
it was subversive.

47
00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:09.071
Maybe they were right.

48
00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:16.036
- What's in this?
- You don't want to know.

49
00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:26.630
[Helicopter Blades Whirring]

50
00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:31.760
Dad. what's wrong?

51
00:08:38.143 --> 00:08:40.352
[Whirring Continues]

52
00:08:40.437 --> 00:08:43.689
What's that Army helicopter doing here?
You said you wouldn't go away again.

53
00:08:43.773 --> 00:08:47.776
- You said you were through.
- I'm not going anywhere.

54
00:08:49.863 --> 00:08:52.281
Promise?

55
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.622
I promise.

56
00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:48.420
Jackson. Harris.

57
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:50.506
Secure the area.

58
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:56.512
John?

59
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.514
John. are you in there?

60
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:04.019
John. come on out.
It's Kirby.

61
00:10:05.939 --> 00:10:10.901
- I know.
- Silent and smooth. just like always.

62
00:10:10.986 --> 00:10:14.697
- I better be. You taught me.
- I'm getting a little rusty.

63
00:10:14.781 --> 00:10:17.950
- What's going on?
- Jenny. how are you?

64
00:10:18.034 --> 00:10:20.035
Hi.

65
00:10:21.788 --> 00:10:25.708
- Jenny. I need to talk to your dad. Okay?
- Yeah? Got a warrant?

66
00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:28.002
- Very funny.
- [Laughs] Jenny.

67
00:10:28.086 --> 00:10:30.087
Okay.

68
00:10:31.673 --> 00:10:34.300
John. we've got a problem.

69
00:10:34.384 --> 00:10:37.219
Someone's killing your men.

70
00:10:37.304 --> 00:10:39.388
You gave them new identities.

71
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:40.889
There must have been a leak.

72
00:10:40.974 --> 00:10:44.727
Lawson. Forrestal.
Bennett have all been hit.

73
00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:48.397
- Who is doing it?
- You've made enemies all over the world.

74
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:50.899
It could have been the Syrians.
the South Americans...

75
00:10:50.984 --> 00:10:53.569
the Russians
or a terrorist group.

76
00:10:54.904 --> 00:10:56.905
They're gonna find you.

77
00:11:00.327 --> 00:11:02.494
We were going
to make a normal life here.

78
00:11:02.579 --> 00:11:04.580
You will. I promise.

79
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:07.082
I'm going into the city to coordinate
with the Federal people.

80
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:09.626
We'll nail those bastards
before they get close to you.

81
00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:13.922
In the meantime. Jackson and Harris
will stay here with you.

82
00:11:14.007 --> 00:11:18.093
- Are they any good?
- Real good. but not as good as you were.

83
00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:26.268
[Sighs]

84
00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:45.412
Is it bad?

85
00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:50.334
I'm not leaving you.
if that's what you mean.

86
00:11:50.418 --> 00:11:53.295
Then it can't be bad.

87
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:22.908
- How bad are you hit?
- I can make it. I'll be all right.

88
00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:26.912
I've got to get my rifle from the shed.
Keep an eye out. They'll be coming.

89
00:12:26.996 --> 00:12:30.666
- [Gunshots]
- Remember. they're downwind.

90
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.751
The air current may
tip them off.

91
00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:36.547
- Downwind? You think
I can smell them coming?
- I did.

92
00:12:38.508 --> 00:12:43.637
Okay. Jenny. you go to your bedroom. okay?
And stay out of sight. I'll be right back.

93
00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:03.449
[Beeps]

94
00:13:31.895 --> 00:13:33.854
Where is she?

95
00:13:33.938 --> 00:13:36.315
Mellow out. man.

96
00:13:36.399 --> 00:13:40.903
We can't talk business with you
waving guns in people's faces.

97
00:13:40.987 --> 00:13:45.324
Your daughter's safe. Colonel.
Whether she stays that way is up to you.

98
00:13:45.408 --> 00:13:47.534
My people got some business
with you.

99
00:13:47.619 --> 00:13:49.620
- [Car Driving Off]
- If you want your kid back...

100
00:13:49.704 --> 00:13:52.247
then you gotta cooperate.

101
00:13:52.332 --> 00:13:54.917
- Right?
- Wrong.

102
00:14:25.823 --> 00:14:28.408
[Grunting]

103
00:15:01.192 --> 00:15:03.652
He's coming at us
with no brakes.

104
00:15:29.220 --> 00:15:32.806
He's still coming. the crazy bastard.
He's gonna hit us.

105
00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:39.354
Shit!

106
00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:47.487
[Explosion]

107
00:15:57.790 --> 00:16:02.377
[Grunting]

108
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:07.841
Don't move. motherfucker.

109
00:16:14.557 --> 00:16:17.017
- Bennett. I thought you were�
- Dead?

110
00:16:18.478 --> 00:16:20.646
You thought wrong.

111
00:16:20.730 --> 00:16:23.357
Ever since you had me
thrown out of your unit...

112
00:16:23.441 --> 00:16:26.318
I've waited to pay you back.

113
00:16:26.402 --> 00:16:29.404
Do you know what today is.
Matrix?

114
00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:33.241
- Payday.
- [Groans]

115
00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:57.099
Tranquilizers.

116
00:16:57.183 --> 00:17:01.061
- I wanted to use the real thing!
- Where's Jenny?

117
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:04.523
Do you remember me.
Colonel?

118
00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:07.818
I remember you. scumbag.

119
00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:10.821
Especially the people
you've tortured and killed.

120
00:17:10.905 --> 00:17:13.615
Colonel Matrix.

121
00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:19.413
You do not understand
a country like Val Verde.

122
00:17:19.497 --> 00:17:22.124
- [Sighs]
- It is a country that needs...

123
00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:26.920
a president who has
an understanding of discipline.

124
00:17:27.004 --> 00:17:29.339
- Why tell me?
- Because...

125
00:17:29.424 --> 00:17:32.884
you're going to return
to Val Verde...

126
00:17:32.969 --> 00:17:35.887
and you are going to kill
the president...

127
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:38.557
that you helped
to overthrow me.

128
00:17:38.641 --> 00:17:40.684
Why don't you
have Bennett do it?

129
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:43.103
Sounds like something
he would get off on.

130
00:17:43.187 --> 00:17:46.898
Because President Velazquez
trusts you. Colonel.

131
00:17:46.983 --> 00:17:50.110
After all. he made you
the hero of the revolution.

132
00:17:50.194 --> 00:17:54.197
Captain Bennett left. shall we say.
under a cloud. Yes?

133
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:57.117
Yeah. He enjoyed killing
a little too much.

134
00:17:57.201 --> 00:17:59.619
Your training. Matrix.

135
00:17:59.704 --> 00:18:03.123
You can get close
to President Velazquez.

136
00:18:03.207 --> 00:18:05.584
You will kill him.

137
00:18:05.668 --> 00:18:08.128
You know. we went
to a lot of trouble to find you.

138
00:18:08.212 --> 00:18:10.422
We had to pretend
Captain Bennett's death...

139
00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:13.967
so that General Kirby would
become agitated and lead us to you...

140
00:18:14.051 --> 00:18:18.263
and now that I have you.
you will do exactly...

141
00:18:18.347 --> 00:18:20.682
as I tell you.

142
00:18:20.767 --> 00:18:23.435
Fuck you.

143
00:18:34.697 --> 00:18:37.073
- Daddy.
- Jenny.

144
00:18:41.662 --> 00:18:43.663
Oh. you bastards.

145
00:18:43.748 --> 00:18:49.002
Colonel Matrix. If you kill President
Velazquez. I will send her back to you.

146
00:18:49.086 --> 00:18:52.631
If you try anything else...

147
00:18:52.715 --> 00:18:55.050
I will mail her to you
in pieces.

148
00:19:05.228 --> 00:19:08.146
- Any sign of Matrix?
- No. sir. Just those bodies.

149
00:19:08.231 --> 00:19:10.148
You think
there's more. sir?

150
00:19:10.233 --> 00:19:13.693
If he's still alive.
I'd expect a lot more.

151
00:19:28.918 --> 00:19:31.253
Sully will make sure
you get on the plane.

152
00:19:32.755 --> 00:19:36.466
Henriques will stay with you.
make sure you get off.

153
00:19:36.551 --> 00:19:40.136
I don't hear from either one
of 'em. she's dead.

154
00:19:40.221 --> 00:19:42.305
How much are they paying you.
Bennett?

155
00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:46.601
They offered me a hundred grand.
You want to know something?

156
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:50.146
When I found out I'd get my hands on you.
I said I'd do it for nothing.

157
00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:55.151
- Hey! Hold it.
- I'll be back. Bennett.

158
00:19:58.781 --> 00:20:00.949
John!

159
00:20:01.033 --> 00:20:03.243
I'll be ready. John.

160
00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:20.343
We're running late.
buddy.

161
00:20:20.428 --> 00:20:22.345
So you and Bennett
met in the service?

162
00:20:22.430 --> 00:20:24.723
Me and Henriques
was in the service too.

163
00:20:24.807 --> 00:20:27.642
There's nothing
like old war buddies.

164
00:20:27.727 --> 00:20:31.062
Well. have a nice
trip now.

165
00:20:31.147 --> 00:20:34.816
Take care. Oh. here. Have some beers
in Val Verde. Matrix.

166
00:20:34.901 --> 00:20:38.445
It'll give everyone a little
more time with your daughter.

167
00:20:38.529 --> 00:20:42.240
- [Laughs]
- You're a funny guy. Sully. I like you.

168
00:20:42.325 --> 00:20:44.242
That's why I'm going
to kill you last.

169
00:20:45.411 --> 00:20:47.746
Move.

170
00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:52.125
Hasta luego. fellas.

171
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:11.478
First class. 7-A.

172
00:21:13.689 --> 00:21:16.358
And you're 7-B. sir.

173
00:21:26.535 --> 00:21:29.537
- Any carry-on luggage?
- Just him.

174
00:21:33.209 --> 00:21:36.127
Open your mouth again.
and I'll nail it shut.

175
00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:40.632
- You must fasten your seat belt. sir.
- Thankyou.

176
00:21:40.716 --> 00:21:44.260
- Could I have a blanket and a pillow. please?
- Sure.

177
00:21:44.345 --> 00:21:46.388
[Mechanical Whir]

178
00:21:51.894 --> 00:21:54.437
- There you go.
- Thank you.

179
00:21:56.190 --> 00:21:58.650
[Woman] Ladies and gentlemen.
we are now preparing for departure.

180
00:21:58.734 --> 00:22:01.403
If you'll please make sure
all your carry-on luggage...

181
00:22:01.487 --> 00:22:03.613
is safely stored
in the overhead compartments.

182
00:22:03.698 --> 00:22:06.866
Make sure your seat belts are fastened
and extinguish all cigarettes.

183
00:22:06.951 --> 00:22:11.079
Once we reach our cruising altitude.
we're gonna be serving our beverages...

184
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:13.164
and then. a little
later on. our dinner.

185
00:22:13.249 --> 00:22:15.500
Shortly after that. we'll be showing
our feature film.

186
00:22:15.584 --> 00:22:18.169
Your flight attendants
are Susan and Lance...

187
00:22:18.254 --> 00:22:20.171
- and I'm Vicky.
- [Cracking]

188
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:22.757
We're here to make your trip
as comfortable as possible.

189
00:22:22.842 --> 00:22:24.843
Thank you. and have a safe
and enjoyable flight.

190
00:22:28.931 --> 00:22:31.891
[Engines Starting]

191
00:22:37.106 --> 00:22:39.524
Excuse me.
How long is the flight?

192
00:22:39.608 --> 00:22:42.277
We land in Val Verde
in exactly 11 hours.

193
00:22:42.361 --> 00:22:44.404
Thank you.
and do me a favor.

194
00:22:44.488 --> 00:22:46.823
Don't disturb my friend.
He's dead tired.

195
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:55.206
Front. please.
Thank you.

196
00:22:55.291 --> 00:22:58.418
Sir. during take off
you must remain seated.

197
00:22:58.502 --> 00:23:00.503
I'm airsick.

198
00:23:22.234 --> 00:23:25.612
[Snarls. Barks]

199
00:25:04.044 --> 00:25:07.338
[Beeping Rapidly]

200
00:25:07.423 --> 00:25:10.758
[Beeping Rhythmically]

201
00:25:53.969 --> 00:25:57.388
Yeah. the bird has flown.
Cargo's aboard.

202
00:25:57.473 --> 00:25:59.891
Now go to the drop-off point.

203
00:25:59.975 --> 00:26:03.478
Yes. Gracias Sully.

204
00:26:06.232 --> 00:26:08.358
Well we are
right on schedule.

205
00:26:08.442 --> 00:26:14.197
With any good fortune. today
will be my last day as a civilian.

206
00:26:14.281 --> 00:26:17.533
[Grunting]

207
00:26:17.618 --> 00:26:19.535
Your father
seems to be cooperating.

208
00:26:19.620 --> 00:26:25.083
You will be together with him soon.
Won't that be nice?

209
00:26:25.167 --> 00:26:29.796
Not nearly as nice as watching him
smash your face in.

210
00:26:32.341 --> 00:26:36.177
Take her below.

211
00:27:04.039 --> 00:27:06.416
[Woman]
Yeah. that Cindy.

212
00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.960
Well. my 7:40 flight
to Vancouver was canceled.

213
00:27:09.044 --> 00:27:13.047
So how about dinner? Yeah.

214
00:27:14.174 --> 00:27:16.676
Well. I could go
to bed early too.

215
00:27:24.435 --> 00:27:27.478
- Maybe we should do it another time.
- Sounds like he's mad at you.

216
00:27:31.066 --> 00:27:33.943
Okay. Well.
I like you too.

217
00:27:34.028 --> 00:27:37.030
All right then.
Talk to you soon. Bye.

218
00:27:37.114 --> 00:27:39.324
Well. love and careers�
It's tough. ain't it?

219
00:27:39.408 --> 00:27:42.243
- Sounds like you need a date.
- Well. I don't.

220
00:27:42.328 --> 00:27:45.038
I thought girls like you
meet a lot of nice boys at airports.

221
00:27:45.122 --> 00:27:47.915
Listen. you're really
bugging me.

222
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:51.252
[No Audible Dialogue]

223
00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:38.633
Hey!

224
00:28:38.717 --> 00:28:40.468
Hey! Slow down.

225
00:28:47.017 --> 00:28:49.727
You know. I got something
I'd really like to give you.

226
00:28:49.812 --> 00:28:52.730
- I'm not interested.
- Oh! You don't know what you're missing.

227
00:28:52.815 --> 00:28:55.274
From here it looks like a nightmare.
Would you leave me alone?

228
00:28:56.318 --> 00:28:59.695
You fucking whore.

229
00:29:00.823 --> 00:29:03.157
[Sighs]

230
00:29:12.835 --> 00:29:14.669
- Don't move!
- [Gasps]

231
00:29:14.753 --> 00:29:18.005
- I'm not going to hurt you. Step aside.
- You said. "Don't move."

232
00:29:18.090 --> 00:29:20.550
Do it. Get in the car.

233
00:29:25.973 --> 00:29:28.516
[Gasps]

234
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.810
[Screams]

235
00:29:36.859 --> 00:29:40.695
- Do exactly what I tell you to do.
- I've got a 7:30 karate class.

236
00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:42.697
- I can't help you.
- You're not gonna make it.

237
00:29:42.781 --> 00:29:45.158
- [Engine Revs]
- [Tires Screeching]

238
00:29:49.913 --> 00:29:52.957
- Follow him.
- [Tires Screeching]

239
00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:56.919
- Oh. I knew you were gonna say that.
- [Engine Starts]

240
00:30:19.276 --> 00:30:23.446
Don't get offended by this question.
but are you gonna kill me or something?

241
00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:26.491
- No.
- I suppose you wouldn't tell me if you were.

242
00:30:26.575 --> 00:30:29.619
- Sure I would.
- Really?

243
